            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The proclamation of these laws and the consequent duty of Israel to keep them (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 26:16",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") constitute a contract between Jehovah and Israel, by which He declares Himself their God, who shall exalt them above other nations, and they declare themselves His people, proper and holy to Him and obliged to obey His laws (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 26:17-19",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ").—In D’s style and the Sg. address (LXX curiously diverges into the Pl. in the last clause of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 26:16",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Deuteronomy 26:16",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). But the argument has been deranged (so all recent commentators; see esp. Cullen, p. 93) either by later additions inappropriately distributed through a misunderstanding of the legal form used, or through the fusion of different conclusions to the Code. See notes below. It is unnecessary to suppose that the passage originally followed ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 27:9",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " f. or 28.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Though the term ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "covenant",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " is not used, the law-giving is regarded as such, as it is implicitly in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 27:9",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " f. and explicitly in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 29:1",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (Deut 28:69). This idea is also implicit in the Code, and is stated explicitly in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 8:18",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 17:3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". So far then, there is no reason for doubting the original character of the passage.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "This is so far an answer to Steuern. who assigns the passage to a later deuteronomist. Wellh. indeed takes ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "this day",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " as that of the Covenant at Ḥoreb, and infers that chs. 12–26 were originally understood as delivered there. On the other hand Berth, finds it probable that we have here the formula under which Josiah bound Israel to observe the Law (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Kings 23:3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", cp. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Jeremiah 11:2",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ff.). For neither of these hypotheses is there any real evidence; and ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "this day",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " is ostensibly the same as that frequently mentioned in the Code and the Introd. Addresses (see on ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 26:16",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Deuteronomy 26:16",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ").",
        "children": []
      },
